[4]
Date: 22 Mar 2003
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Centers for Disease Control and Prevention SARS update 21 Mar 2003
<http://www.cdc.gov/od/oc/media/sars.htm>

Severe acute respiratory syndrome
---------------------------------
Report of suspected cases under investigation in the United States: numbers
of suspected cases are expected to fluctuate as additional information
becomes available.
State: suspected cases under investigation*
California: 6
Hawaii: 3
Maine: 1
Massachusetts: 1
New Jersey: 1
New Mexico: 1
North Carolina: 2
New York: 2
Rhode Island: 1
Utah: 1
Virginia: 2
Wisconsin: 1
Total suspected cases under investigation 22
*Case definition <http://www.cdc.gov/ncidod/sars/casedefinition.htm>
[According to a press briefing on 21 Mar 2003
(<http://www.cdc.gov/od/oc/media/transcripts/t030321.htm>) there are 3
possible cases in close contacts of suspected SARS cases. "In one cluster,
an individual who traveled to Asia may have been the source of infection in
2 health care workers who provided care, and in the second situation, one
person who traveled to Asia may have been the source of infection in a
family member." In addition, there was mention that 2 of the 22 suspected
cases mentioned above had a history of staying on the 9th floor of the
Kowloon Hotel implicated in the original transmission of SARS in Hong
Kong.The CDC SARS website has information on recommended isolation and
infection control and information on respiratory protection for patient
management. <http://www.cdc.gov/ncidod/sars/>. - Mod.MPP]
