Elizabeth <SmithE@bioport.com>, Debra Mohon <txhorses@msn.com>, Folkers,
Greg <GFOLKERS@niaid.nih.gov>.
In this update we are presenting the latest available numbers of suspected
cases of SARS. As of the time of this report (22 Mar 2003 5:30 PM EST)
there are 386 cases with 11 deaths reported to WHO from 14 countries.
According to the newswires there was another death in a case from Canada.
To date cases continue to occur among close contacts of previously
identified SARS cases. With the implementation of infection control
precautions in the hospital setting, it appears as though transmission to
health workers involved in the care of SARS patients has been markedly
reduced. - Mod.MPP]
